    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/104.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Imperial Government will move action of Bundesrat authorized in article 46 but
                    suggests all interested parties confer and come to an amicable agreement. I have
                    answered that such arrangement satisfactory if voluntarily accepted by American
                    contractors, but that American remonstrances against effects of the law must
                    continue until relief is had. I have called attention to option of extension of
                    contracts and pressed for action in time for its exercise before July 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
